# VoiceSlide — NLP Presentation Automation Tool

> **End-to-end workflow using 100 % free & open-source technologies.**
> Each phase ends with a visible, testable deliverable. The agent will pause after every phase for your approval before continuing.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Development strategy**: Phases 1–10 use **sample test slides** so each feature can be tested in isolation. The slide import system (Phase 2) ensures the final product accepts **any user-provided presentation**. All subsequent features are data-driven and work on whatever slides are loaded.

---

## Tech Stack Overview

| Layer | Technology | License |
|---|---|---|
| Presentation Engine | **reveal.js** | MIT |
| Slide Data Format | **JSON** (`slides.json`) — data-driven, no hardcoded HTML | — |
| Slide Import (`.pptx`) | **python-pptx** | MIT |
| Speech-to-Text (local) | **faster-whisper** (streamed via WebSocket) | MIT |
| Intent Classification | **sentence-transformers** (cosine similarity on command embeddings) | Apache 2.0 |
| Semantic Search | **sentence-transformers** (all-MiniLM-L6-v2) | Apache 2.0 |
| Keyword Highlighting | **fuzzball** (fuzzy string matching) + emphasis-phrase detection | MIT |
| Summarization | **distilbart-cnn-12-6** (lazy-loaded) | MIT |
| Sentiment & Filler Analysis | **VADER** (vaderSentiment) | MIT |
| Translation | **MarianMT** (Helsinki-NLP) or **LibreTranslate** | Apache 2.0 / AGPL-3.0 |
| Q&A Retrieval | **sentence-transformers** + cosine similarity | Apache 2.0 |
| Backend | **Flask** + **Flask-SocketIO** | BSD |
| Analytics Charts | **Chart.js** | MIT |
| Frontend | **HTML / CSS / JS** | — |
| Package Manager | **pip** / **npm** | — |

> [!NOTE]
> Every library above is installable via `pip` or `npm` with zero API keys required.

